{
  "stem": "12491.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We were lucky that we did not have to go through that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And this is-- this would lasted till approximately March, 1941.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In March, 1941, there was an edict issued that all Jews will have to move to a ghetto which is across the river from Krakow in a little town named Podgorze.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I'm not going to spell it because it difficult.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they-- they formed-- they-- they formed a ghetto there and so-- moved out all Polish people from a large section of that-- part-- of that part of Krakow town, surrounded it by walls, and moved the Jews in, and also moved people into that ghetto which were not from Krakow, which were from small towns surrounding Krakow.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But since I had contacts through sports clubs and other places with people who eventually-- Jewish people who wound up to be all Polish-- Jewish policemen.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They call them [? firemen, ?] [? alderman, ?] and things like that, and all who worked in an office which was distributing jobs in German facilities.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I managed to organize jobs which were acceptable to the Germans and therefore made you, for the time being, at least, rather safe from evacuation from ghetto.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Hm? ?]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We rented wagon with two wheels, which I was the horse of, and pulled it into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was quite a distance from where we lived.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we took only the absolute necessary thing, because the place which we were assigned in ghetto was very small.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were fortunate.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were assigned a room and a kitchen without having another family living with us, because in many cases, an apartment like that-- a room and a kitchen-- was occupied by two or three families.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
